      id: 'hvn',
      title: "HVN",
      category: 'orderflow',
      lectureNumber: null,
      content: "# HVN\n\n**Tags:** `#profile-levels` `#orderflow`\n**Links:** [[Orderflow/Volume Profile]] · [[Orderflow/TPO and Market Profile]] · [[Orderflow/AMT]]\n\n---\n\n## High Volume Node\n\nA local peak in the volume profile where significant volume accumulated. Represents acceptance and fair value.\n\n**Properties:**\n- Two-sided trade occurred here — order flow balanced\n- Price slows or rotates when revisiting HVNs (friction zone)\n- Memory points for participation — institutions remember these levels\n- Use: expect consolidation and mean-reversion around HVNs\n\n---\n\n**See also:** [[Orderflow/Volume Profile]] · [[Orderflow/TPO and Market Profile]] · [[Orderflow/AMT]] · [[Lectures/Phase-4-Order-Flow/L18 - Market Profile and AMT]]\n",
      wikilinks: ["Orderflow/Volume Profile","Orderflow/TPO and Market Profile","Orderflow/AMT","Orderflow/Volume Profile","Orderflow/TPO and Market Profile","Orderflow/AMT","Lectures/Phase-4-Order-Flow/L18 - Market Profile and AMT"],
