      lectureNumber: null,
      content: "# Initial Balance\n\n**Tags:** `#profile-levels` `#orderflow`\n**Links:** [[Orderflow/Volume Profile]] · [[Orderflow/TPO and Market Profile]] · [[Orderflow/AMT]]\n\n---\n\n## Initial Balance\n\nThe price range established in the first hour (or first 2 TPO brackets) of the regular trading session.\n\n**Properties:**\n- Sets the daily context and tone\n- Wide IB = strong directional flow, expect range extensions\n- Narrow IB = uncertainty, balanced conditions likely\n- IB boundaries often act as key intraday support/resistance\n\n**Extension Target:**\n```\nIB Extension = IBhigh/low ± 2 × IBrange\n```\n\n---\n\n**See also:** [[Orderflow/Volume Profile]] · [[Orderflow/TPO and Market Profile]] · [[Orderflow/AMT]] · [[Lectures/Phase-4-Order-Flow/L18 - Market Profile and AMT]]\n",
